JOHANNESBURG - From mechanics, to drivers, to fans, motorsport is dominated by men, however Tasmin Pepper has not paid attention to this statistic. She has been racing since she was a toddler and is paving the way for other aspiring women drivers. The 27-year-old who has been racing for nearly two decades now started out with karting. READ: Karting women on track for domination She competed in various competitions around the world including the Asian Formula BMW championship. eNCA sports reporter Shahied Joseph caught up with Miss Pepper at Kyalami. eNCA